  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Cut the<strong> sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin <strong>chips&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to&nbsp;a large baking tray, sprinkle with the <strong>cornflour</strong> and drizzle with&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: the cornflour helps the chips crisp up!</p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good old mix up (use clean hands)</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven&nbsp;for 20 min or until the chips&nbsp;are tender and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>chicken</strong>&nbsp;<strong>breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> to a bowl with the&nbsp;<strong>smoked paprika, dried oregano, cayenne </strong><strong>pepper</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong>&nbsp;</strong>and plenty&nbsp;of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a lid, with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat and cook for 2-3 min on each side</p>\r\n<p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> to the pan, cover and cook for 10-12 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim and slice the<strong> spring onions</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Peel and chop the <strong>shallot</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, melt a large knob of&nbsp;<strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once melted, add the <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>shallot</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until soft</p>\r\n<p>Drain the <strong>sweetcorn</strong> and add it to the softened <strong>shallot</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>clotted cream</strong> and cook for 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Season generously with both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add&nbsp;the <strong>sweetcorn</strong> to a&nbsp;<strong>food processor&nbsp;</strong>and blitz to a coarse&nbsp;pur&eacute;e&nbsp;- this is your <strong>creamed corn</strong></p>\r\n<p>Return the <strong>creamed corn</strong> back to the pot and set aside&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/806.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
